choices.text:
, why isn't my government increasing the salaries of nurses, than we will have enough of them to help some of the babies that mothers have lost or were unable to attend hospital due to labour?

ntsalu Napsi April 21, 2017 at 9:55 pm

We have this problem in my country Zambia every 3 days a newborn dies and 5% of the mothers die. Why are politicians and the government so heartless not to have passed the 5,000USD salary which is the least a professional nurse requires to reach someone in area like Kapiri mposhi. us nurses have thought of going on strike if not address by Friday.. Sorry we also need to eat just like people requesting on your Facebook page. We work at 6PM till 6AM; each night. we have gone through Nursing school so much with tears, crying, anger that's we always throw at any man whatsoever. We don't want money from you Alex we want a bakasa to take care of us nurses once we go on strike by Friday so we can attend to you and your family with ease alex forget about those medical aids you still have papa how can you never care about any nurse that cares about sick person's life. it's about us for we have lost patience with tired online requests, treats and appeals to people and government when we carry your ridiculous Democratic Republic of Mothers and Fathers.

Please share how we can turn the around. Would greatly appreciate.
